## Stage 0: injected page script

The injected script at the top of the `new-blog.artlist[.]io` HTML used a compact wrapper:

```javascript
var blob = atob("...");
var key = 80;
var bytes = new Uint8Array(blob.length);
for (...) bytes[i] = blob.charCodeAt(i) ^ key;
(new Function(new TextDecoder().decode(bytes)))();
```

The decoded script was an EtherHiding loader. The page stores contract lookup logic instead of a fixed payload host, allowing the contract value to rotate the next-stage server on-chain.

The decoded loader also sets a guard flag:

```javascript
if (window["_197515e445"]) return;
window["_197515e445"] = 1;
```

This prevents duplicate execution on the same page.

