The successful API, ray, `/7z`, and archive responses set no cookies. The failed `.zip`-suffix request alone returned `403` with `xdv_sess`, indicating a separate denial/session route. The working flow appears tied to the ray/token and server-side request context such as source address, `vid`, or request history.

The inner PowerShell waits 20 seconds before fetching `/7z` and the archive. The successful replay preserved that delay. It may act as a timing gate or simply give the backend time to stage the archive.

With a fresh ray, the intended request order, and no early `/p/<archive-token>` request, the archive delivered successfully:

