```

The message switch handles `WM_COPYDATA` (`0x4a`) as the main control path. `WM_CLOSE`/`WM_DESTROY`-style values `0x10` and `0x02` reach short close/return branches; `WM_ENDSESSION` (`0x16`) runs cleanup and `ExitProcess(0)`; `WM_WTSSESSION_CHANGE` (`0x2b1`) is allowed by the range check but currently falls through to the default `DefWindowProc` path.

